The paper discusses programming models for concurrency, which is a topic that falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the trade-off between preventing data race errors and allowing data parallelism, which is a topic that falls under the operating systems (cs.OS), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories.
